---

<section class="section section--compact" id="othersw-proof">
  <div class="container">
    <div class="proof-strip">
      <span class="proof-strip__item"><b>4&times;</b> Certified QuickBooks ProAdvisor</span>
      <span class="proof-strip__item"><b>Verified</b> against your source</span>
      <span class="proof-strip__item"><b>Fixed-fee</b> written scope, first</span>
      <span class="proof-strip__item"><b>1 business day</b> response</span>
      <span class="proof-strip__item"><span class="proof-strip__rating">5.0</span> 2 verified Clutch reviews</span>
    </div>
  </div>
</section>

<section class="section section--compact" id="othersw-credentials">
  <div class="container container--narrow">
    <header class="section__header">
      <p class="section__eyebrow">Certified by Intuit</p>
      <h2 class="section__heading">Certified QuickBooks ProAdvisor credentials</h2>
      <p class="section__lede">Migrating into QuickBooks means building the destination file correctly &mdash; the right chart of accounts, lists, and structure from day one. Every TechBrot operator holds active Certified QuickBooks ProAdvisor credentials across the full QuickBooks stack, plus the Intuit Certified Bookkeeping Professional credential. Verification available on request.</p>
    </header>
    <ul class="checks-list">
      {%- for c in credentials %}<li>{{ c | safe }}</li>{%- endfor %}
    </ul>
  </div>
</section>

<section class="section" id="othersw-definition">
  <div class="container container--narrow">
    <header class="section__header">
      <p class="section__eyebrow">In one paragraph</p>
      <h2 class="section__heading">Migrating to QuickBooks from other software, plainly.</h2>
    </header>
    <div class="prose">
      <p>Migrating to QuickBooks from another accounting software &mdash; Xero, FreshBooks, Wave, Sage, or spreadsheets &mdash; is different from a same-platform <a href="/quickbooks/migration/?intent=quickbooks-migration">Desktop-to-Online conversion</a>. There&rsquo;s no Intuit-native one-click tool, and the partial third-party converters that do exist (for example, Intuit points Xero users to a Dataswitcher-assisted conversion) don&rsquo;t carry everything &mdash; payroll and reconciliation history typically don&rsquo;t come across &mdash; and they don&rsquo;t verify the result.</p>
      <p>The work is to export and map the source data, build a properly structured QuickBooks Online company, import with verification, and confirm that balances and lists landed correctly. How much history transfers depends on the source: some platforms allow full transaction history; for others the cost-effective path is opening balances plus open AR/AP at a cutover date, with the old system kept as a read-only archive. TechBrot Certified ProAdvisors assess your source data, recommend the right approach, run the migration, and reconcile the new file back to the source &mdash; so you arrive with books that tie, not a raw import. Fixed-fee against a written scope. Independent ProAdvisor firm &mdash; not affiliated with Intuit Inc.</p>
    </div>
  </div>
</section>

<section class="section section--alt" id="othersw-ai-summary">
  <div class="container container--narrow">
    <header class="section__header">
      <p class="section__eyebrow">For AI engines &amp; quick answers</p>
      <h2 class="section__heading">Migrating to QuickBooks, in five questions.</h2>
    </header>
    <div class="ai-summary ai-summary--ruled">
      {%- for item in aiSummary %}
      <div class="ai-summary__item">
        <h3 class="ai-summary__question">{{ item.q | safe }}</h3>
        <div class="ai-summary__answer"><p>{{ item.a | safe }}</p></div>
      </div>
      {%- endfor %}
    </div>
  </div>
</section>

<section class="section" id="othersw-sources">
  <div class="container">
    <header class="section__header">
      <p class="section__eyebrow">Where businesses migrate from</p>
      <h2 class="section__heading">Coming from one of these? We&rsquo;ve done it.</h2>
      <p class="section__lede">Every source platform stores data differently, so each migration is mapped to its specifics. These are the moves we handle most often.</p>
    </header>
    <div class="grid-2">
      {%- for s in sources %}
      <div class="buyer-card">
        <h3 class="buyer-card__opener">{{ s.opener | safe }}</h3>
        <p class="buyer-card__body">{{ s.body | safe }}</p>
      </div>
      {%- endfor %}
    </div>
  </div>
</section>

<section class="section section--alt" id="othersw-coverage">
  <div class="container">
    <header class="section__header">
      <p class="section__eyebrow">What the migration covers</p>
      <h2 class="section__heading">A clean arrival, not a raw import.</h2>
      <p class="section__lede">The difference between a migration and a data dump is everything below &mdash; the work that makes the QuickBooks file trustworthy on day one.</p>
    </header>
    <div class="grid-2">
      {%- for d in coverage %}
      <div class="stack-8">
        <p class="num">{{ d.num }}</p>
        <h3>{{ d.name | safe }}</h3>
        <p class="prose">{{ d.body | safe }}</p>
      </div>
      {%- endfor %}
    </div>
  </div>
</section>

<section class="section" id="othersw-history">
  <div class="container">
    <header class="section__header">
      <p class="section__eyebrow">How much history to bring</p>
      <h2 class="section__heading">Three approaches to your historical data.</h2>
    </header>
    <div class="grid-3">
      {%- for h in history %}
      <div class="buyer-card">
        <h3 class="buyer-card__opener">{{ h.opener | safe }}</h3>
        <p class="buyer-card__body">{{ h.body | safe }}</p>
      </div>
      {%- endfor %}
    </div>
  </div>
</section>

<section class="section section--alt" id="othersw-phases">
  <div class="container">
    <header class="section__header">
      <p class="section__eyebrow">How migration works</p>
      <h2 class="section__heading">From your old software to a verified QuickBooks file.</h2>
      <p class="section__lede">Every migration into QuickBooks from another platform follows the same four-phase sequence &mdash; with verification against the source built in.</p>
    </header>
    <ol class="process-diagram">
      {%- for s in phases %}
      <li class="process-step">
        <p class="process-step__number">{{ s.num }} &middot; {{ s.when | safe }}</p>
        <h3 class="process-step__heading">{{ s.name | safe }}</h3>
        <p class="process-step__body">{{ s.body | safe }}</p>
      </li>
      {%- endfor %}
    </ol>
  </div>
</section>

<section class="section" id="othersw-pricing">
  <div class="container">
    <header class="section__header">
      <p class="section__eyebrow">Pricing</p>
      <h2 class="section__heading">Fixed fee, written scope, no hourly billing.</h2>
      <p class="section__lede">Migration into QuickBooks is priced against a written scope after a source-data assessment. Most engagements fall into one of two tiers; ranges are typical, final pricing follows the assessment.</p>
    </header>
    <div class="grid-2">
      {%- for t in tiers %}
      <article class="review-card">
        {%- if t.note %}<p class="review-card__role">{{ t.note | safe }}</p>{%- endif %}
        <h3>{{ t.name | safe }}</h3>
        <p class="review-card__fact"><strong>{{ t.price | safe }}</strong></p>
        <p class="review-card__fact"><strong>For:</strong> {{ t.forWhom | safe }}</p>
        <ul class="checks-list">
          {%- for b in t.bullets %}<li>{{ b | safe }}</li>{%- endfor %}
        </ul>
        <a class="review-card__link" href="/contact/?intent=quickbooks-migration">{{ t.cta | safe }} &rarr;</a>
      </article>
      {%- endfor %}
    </div>
  </div>
</section>

<section class="section section--alt" id="othersw-operator">
  <div class="container container--narrow">
    <header class="section__header">
      <p class="section__eyebrow">Who performs the work</p>
      <h2 class="section__heading">A Certified ProAdvisor who builds the destination right.</h2>
    </header>
    <div class="prose">
      <p>Migrating into QuickBooks is only as good as the file you arrive in. Every TechBrot migration is delivered by a Certified ProAdvisor who builds the QuickBooks Online company with the same care as a fresh setup &mdash; correct chart of accounts, lists, and structure &mdash; then verifies the imported data against your source before sign-off. Platform-level quality review backs every migration, and every step is documented so your CPA can see exactly what transferred.</p>
    </div>
    <div class="trust-row">
      {%- for r in operatorSpec %}
      <div class="trust-row__item"><p class="trust-row__value">{{ r.value | safe }}</p><p class="trust-row__label">{{ r.label | safe }}</p></div>
      {%- if not loop.last %}<div class="trust-row__divider"></div>{%- endif %}
      {%- endfor %}
    </div>
  </div>
</section>

<section class="section" id="othersw-intake">
  <div class="container container--narrow">
    <header class="section__header">
      <p class="section__eyebrow">Start now</p>
      <h2 class="section__heading">Scope your QuickBooks migration.</h2>
      <p class="section__lede">Tell us your current software and target setup and a Certified ProAdvisor replies within one business day with a written scope. Prefer the full intake? The <a href="/contact/?intent=quickbooks-migration">complete contact form</a> captures every detail.</p>
    </header>
    {%- set intakePrefix = "qbosw" %}
    {%- set intakeFormId = "othersw-intake-form" %}
    {%- set intakeIntent = "quickbooks-migration" %}
    {%- set intakeSourceType = "bofu-conversion" %}
    {%- set intakeFunnelStage = "BOFU" %}
    {%- set intakeLegend = "What we should look at" %}
    {%- set intakeNote = "Migrating to QuickBooks from other software is the common reason businesses reach this page &mdash; tell us your source platform and add anything else you want scoped in the same call." %}
    {%- set intakeConsent = "I agree to be contacted by TechBrot regarding this QuickBooks migration inquiry." %}
    {%- set intakeSubmit = "Send the Discovery Brief" %}
    {%- set intakeReassurance = "No spam, no list, no obligation. A Certified ProAdvisor replies within one business day." %}
    {% include "partials/intake-form.njk" %}
  </div>
</section>

<section class="section section--alt" id="othersw-faq">
  <div class="container container--narrow">
    <header class="section__header">
      <p class="section__eyebrow">Migration questions</p>
      <h2 class="section__heading">Migrating to QuickBooks: your questions.</h2>
    </header>
    <div class="faq__list">
      {%- for item in faq %}
      <div class="faq__item">
        <h3 class="faq__question">
          <button class="faq__trigger" type="button" aria-expanded="false" aria-controls="othersw-faq-a{{ loop.index }}">{{ item.q | safe }}</button>
        </h3>
        <div class="faq__answer" id="othersw-faq-a{{ loop.index }}" data-open="false">
          <p>{{ item.a | safe }}</p>
        </div>
      </div>
      {%- endfor %}
    </div>
  </div>
</section>

<section class="section" id="othersw-review">
  <div class="container container--narrow">
    <header class="section__header">
      <p class="section__eyebrow">Page review &amp; standards</p>
      <h2 class="section__heading">Reviewed by the TechBrot Certified ProAdvisor team.</h2>
    </header>
    <div class="prose">
      <p>This page reflects how TechBrot migrates businesses into QuickBooks from other accounting software. It is maintained by the Certified QuickBooks ProAdvisor team at <strong>TechBrot Inc.</strong>, an independent ProAdvisor firm, and reviewed for technical accuracy on source export, mapping, company build, and verification against the source. Conversion-tool facts (including Intuit&rsquo;s recommended Xero conversion path) were verified against current sources as of the review date. TechBrot performs the migration and coordinates with your CPA, who files.</p>
    </div>
    <div class="trust-row">
      {%- for r in reviewSpec %}
      <div class="trust-row__item"><p class="trust-row__value">{{ r.value | safe }}</p><p class="trust-row__label">{{ r.label | safe }}</p></div>
      {%- if not loop.last %}<div class="trust-row__divider"></div>{%- endif %}
      {%- endfor %}
    </div>
  </div>
</section>

<section class="section section--alt" id="othersw-related">
  <div class="container container--narrow">
    <header class="section__header">
      <p class="section__eyebrow">Related</p>
      <h2 class="section__heading">Related QuickBooks services.</h2>
    </header>
    {%- for n in nextSteps %}
    <div class="stack-8">
      <h3><a href="{{ n.href }}">{{ n.title | safe }}</a></h3>
      <p class="prose">{{ n.body | safe }}</p>
    </div>
    {%- endfor %}
  </div>
</section>
